      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STARLIGHT SASS (7) has been excellent of late and she made it two in a row when successful at her latest appearance over 1720m at Penrith, getting home by 3 metres. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Needs to be at her best to beat this field but she is up to the challenge. ROLL TO THE TOP (1) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 4.5 metres from the winner in second over 1720m at Dubbo. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Steps up a level but she is good enough to take this out. VAMOS (6) finished eighth last start at Listed level in a race won by Seasider over 2260m at Bathurst, beaten 11 metres. A return to form is on the cards. TAKE OUT (4) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish third at Bathurst over 1730m.",
